\par <I> <h> <#/>Let the Factory Close </h>
\par <#/>It was two-fifteen when Arita woke up in response to the door bell. <#/>All was quiet, even the refrigerator motor had groaned itself to exhaustion and was now silent. <#/>The bell rang a second time. <#/>Then she heard the usual complaints.
\par <#/>"Why are you taking so long to open? <#/>Have I disturbed you?"
\par <#/>Eyes closed, lips tightly shut, Arita moved to
wards the front door automatically. <#/>She did not want to speak to anyone. <#/>Aware that her system was allergic to the night air that flowed into it by mouth, however briefly she may have been asleep, Arita did not answer either of the two questions. 
<
