had not had time to read that disturbing day, she ran to the room she shared with her sister, locked the door and dropped her bag and the newspaper on the bed. <#/>She needed peace. <#/>She picked up her Bible then put it down again. <#/>To her, even God 
seemed to have taken sides with those fighting against her mother. <#/>She picked up her bag and put it on the floor. <#/>She picked up the newspaper, intending to drop it on the floor too. <#/>Then a headline on the back page caught her eye:
